Sir Martin SorrellFounder and CEO of WPPLocationLondon, United KingdomIndustryMarketing and AdvertisingCurrentWPPEducationHarvard Business SchoolInfluencerView Sir Martin’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Sir Martin’s Full ProfileSir Martin’s Posts & ActivityThe Press needs (and...Sir Martin Sorrell on LinkedInMarch 13, 2017See 32 more postsAt the Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity...Sir Martin sharedDelighted to have been named among LinkedIn's Top Voices of...Sir Martin sharedRisk-aversion and short-termism rule in the world’s...Sir Martin sharedSee all activitySummaryIn 1985 Martin Sorrell took a controlling stake in Wire & Plastic Products, a small UK manufacturer of shopping baskets and teapots. Today WPP is the world leader in advertising and marketing services, and proud parent to many of the industry's biggest and most admired agencies. The group employs over 200,000 people in 112 countries, and its clients include 360 of the Fortune Global 500, all 30 of the Dow Jones 30 and 78 of the NASDAQ 100. In 2016, Sir Martin was named Britain’s best-performing CEO and the second best-performing CEO in the world by Harvard Business Review.ExperienceChief ExecutiveWPP1985  –  Present (32 years)EducationHarvard Business SchoolUniversity of CambridgeView Sir Martin’s full profile to...See who you know in commonGet introducedContact Sir Martin directlyView Sir Martin’s Full ProfileView this profile in another languageEnglishGermanPeople Also ViewedWinnie ByanyimaExecutive Director at OxfamJeff WeinerCEO at LinkedIneric salamaceo at Kantar GroupLuisa ZissmanDirector at UK CandylipzLeah TottonDirector & co-owner Dr Leah Cosmetic Clinics. Winner of The Apprentice. Medical DoctorDavid CameronFormer Prime Minister of the United KingdomMark CubanPresidentBill GatesCo-chair, Bill & Melinda Gates FoundationPeter JonesChief Executive Officer at JessopsScott SpiritChief Digital Officer at 